Update the scrollbar styling in `src/styles/staffglobal.css`.

Goal:
Fix scrollable card sections so vertical and horizontal scrollbars do not push the content left, up, or off-centre when scrolling appears.

Requirements:
1. Find all shared scrollable card, table, panel, modal, dropdown, page, and content wrapper styles in `staffglobal.css`.
2. Add a stable scrollbar layout system using:

scrollbar-gutter: stable both-edges;

3. Apply this only to elements that use:
- overflow: auto;
- overflow: scroll;
- overflow-x: auto;
- overflow-y: auto;

4. Keep the content visually centred inside cards, even when both horizontal and vertical scrollbars are active.
5. Add box-sizing: border-box where needed so scrollbar spacing does not break widths/heights.
6. Do not change routes, API files, database logic, React components, or authentication.
7. Keep the change inside `staffglobal.css` only.
8. Make the scrollbar styling match the current Apple-style liquid glass UI.

Add or update scrollbar styling like this where suitable:

.card-scroll-section,
.scroll-panel,
.table-scroll,
.dropdown-scroll,
.modal-scroll,
.staff-scroll-area {
  overflow: auto;
  scrollbar-gutter: stable both-edges;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  scrollbar-width: thin;
}

.card-scroll-section::-webkit-scrollbar,
.scroll-panel::-webkit-scrollbar,
.table-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar,
.dropdown-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar,
.modal-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar,
.staff-scroll-area::-webkit-scrollbar {
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
}

.card-scroll-section::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb,
.scroll-panel::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb,
.table-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb,
.dropdown-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb,
.modal-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb,
.staff-scroll-area::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  border-radius: 999px;
  background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb, 120, 120, 120), 0.28);
}

.card-scroll-section::-webkit-scrollbar-track,
.scroll-panel::-webkit-scrollbar-track,
.table-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track,
.dropdown-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track,
.modal-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track,
.staff-scroll-area::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
  background: transparent;
}

Important:
Use the real class names already inside `staffglobal.css`, do not create unused CSS unless a shared class is already needed.
Make sure both vertical and horizontal scrollbars can exist together without shifting card content.
After making the change, check the showcase section and any shared scroll examples in `staffglobal.css` so the scrollbar behaviour is shown there too.

